questions.question: What is the main difference between model parameters and hyperparameters in machine learning?
options: Hyperparameters are set before training, while model parameters are learned during training.
Both model parameters and hyperparameters are learned during training.
Both model parameters and hyperparameters are set before training.
Model parameters are set before training, while hyperparameters are learned during training.
correct_answers: Hyperparameters are set before training, while model parameters are learned during training.
